<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Pausing multiple audio elements.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4633&amp;p=7151#p7151"><![CDATA[
You could have just a single audio element and set the new src on it, it will cause the currently playing audio to unload when loading the new one.<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>        &lt;script src=&quot;js/modernizr-1.7.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;<br />      &lt;script&gt;<br />         var audioElement = Modernizr.audio ? new Audio() : null;<br />         function playSong(songname) {<br />            if (audioElement &amp;&amp; Modernizr.audio.ogg){<br />                    var songfile = 'ogg/'+ songname + '.ogg';<br />                    audioElement.src = songfile;<br />                    audioElement.play();<br />               } <br />                  else if (audioElement &amp;&amp; Modernizr.audio.mp3){<br />                    var songfile = 'mp3/' + songname + '.mp3';<br />                    audioElement.src = songfile;<br />                    audioElement.play();<br />                  }<br />         }<br />      &lt;/script&gt;<br /></code></dd></dl><br />Or you could create one audio element for each clip in an array or object (or in the document) and pause them when playing a new one.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Sun May 08, 2011 7:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
