Hi guys,<br /><br />I have created several audio elements using this code.<br /><br />function<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>        &lt;script src=&quot;js/modernizr-1.7.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;<br />      &lt;script&gt;<br />         function playSong(songname) {<br />            if (Modernizr.audio &amp;&amp; Modernizr.audio.ogg){<br />                    var songfile = 'ogg/'+ songname + '.ogg';<br />                    audioElement = new Audio(songfile);<br />                    audioElement.play();<br />               } <br />                  else if (Modernizr.audio &amp;&amp; Modernizr.audio.mp3){<br />                    var songfile = 'mp3/' + songname + '.mp3';<br />                    audioElement = new Audio(songfile);<br />                    audioElement.play();<br />                  }<br />         }<br />      &lt;/script&gt;</code></dd></dl><br />Html that calls the function<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;ul&gt; <br />                  &lt;li onClick=&quot;playSong('wakeupcallpreview');&quot;&gt;01. Wake Up Call&lt;/li&gt;<br />                        &lt;li onClick=&quot;playSong('cheatinghandspreview');&quot;&gt;02. Cheatin Hands&lt;/li&gt;<br />                        &lt;li onClick=&quot;playSong('hellintownpreview');&quot;&gt;03. Hell in Town&lt;/li&gt;<br />                        &lt;li onClick=&quot;playSong('mrsunpreview');&quot;&gt;04. Mr. Sun&lt;/li&gt;<br />                        &lt;li onClick=&quot;playSong('whycantyoutellmepreview');&quot;&gt;05. Why Can't You Tell Me?&lt;/li&gt;<br />                        &lt;/ul&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />As you can see, i can make a file play, but irritatingly you can play one file on top of another. What is a good way of pause() ing all audio elements made? <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />I would like to do something like (in english)<br /><br />allAudio.pause()<br /> 